Lyon said the fee for Lacazette, who recently broke into the French national team, was the highest ever achieved by the club in a transfer. PARIS - Shares in Olympique Lyonnais rose on Thursday after the French soccer club announced the sale of striker Alexandre Lacazette to Arsenal for a fee of up to $68 million.Lyon said the fee for Lacazette, who recently broke into the French national team, was the highest ever achieved by the club in a transfer.Olympique Lyon shares were up 1.3% in early trading.The French soccer club, which won the last of its seven Ligue 1 championship titles in 2008, first listed on the Paris stock market in 2007.